HEADWORD: introverted
<hw>in"tro*vert`ed</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>examining one's
own sensory and perceptual experiences. Contrasted with
<ant>extrospective</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> introspective.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>marked by concern predominantly with oneself or
one's own feelings. Contrasted with
<contr>extroverted</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> introvert, introvertive.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>introvertish</ent>⟦br⟧
